descp2: array-like of float, shape = (n_samples, n_classes) or (n_samples,) Predicted probabilities, as returned by a classifier's predict_proba method. If ``y_pred.shape = (n_samples,)`` the probabilities provided are assumed to be that of the positive class. The labels in ``y_pred`` are assumed to be ordered alphabetically, as done by :class:`preprocessing.LabelBinarizer`.
